This repository is a game project driven by **GAT**, a full-cycle Godot game-dev workflow
(design → style-lock → assets → implement → verify), with a self-evolving knowledge base.
Codex: read this file every session. The authoritative rules are in
`{{GAT_HOME}}/runtimes/claude/RULES.md` — follow them.

## How to run a GAT skill in Codex

Each GAT skill is a Markdown procedure at `{{GAT_HOME}}/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`. To run one,
**read that file and execute its steps** with the user's arguments. Custom prompts have been
installed at `~/.codex/prompts/gat-*.md` so you can invoke them as `/gat-<name>`.

| Skill | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `gat-workflow-start` | inspect repo, recommend next step |
| `gat-brainstorm` / `gat-story` / `gat-design` / `gat-milestone` | design pre-production docs |
| `gat-style-lock` | freeze the enforceable Style Contract ⭐ |
| `gat-asset` / `gat-vfx` | generate style-locked art / skill VFX |
| `gat-scaffold` / `gat-implement` | Godot project skeleton / build a milestone ⭐ |
| `gat-verify` | smoke + balance sim + style audit + coverage |
| `gat-evolve` / `gat-learn-from-ref` | self-evolving loop / study reference games |

## Roles

Play the role the current phase needs (definitions in `{{GAT_HOME}}/agents/*.md`): designer,
writer, planner, artist/vfx-artist, engineer, qa, curator. Codex runs these sequentially rather
than as parallel subagents; the steps are the same.

## Non-negotiables (summary — full text in RULES.md)

1. No asset without a locked `design/art/style-contract.yaml`; compose via
   `{{GAT_HOME}}/tools/style_prompt.py`, gate via `{{GAT_HOME}}/tools/art_audit.py`. Off-style →
   regenerate.
2. Read the GDD + `knowledge/architecture/*` before coding. One milestone at a time.
3. Honest verification: it ran, numbers from the sim, assets exist and on-style, design covered —
   with evidence. Never claim done without a run.
4. Content in `data/*.json`, logic in code, art registered; decouple via EventBus.
5. Respect an open editor (Hastur smoke, no headless import) and the dedicated test save slot.
6. Self-evolving: read `knowledge/wiki/*` + `.gat/journal.md` before, write back via `gat-evolve`
   after. Edit the KB freely; only propose skill/template edits.
7. Reference study is learning-only; commercial use of that module needs approval; no DRM
   circumvention.

